@MITDriverless believes this will be critical for avoiding collisions and for maneuvering to safety on highways which will result in countless saved lives.  
#motorsports #MITDriveressIAC2021 #SelfDrivingCars #IAC2021 #Autonomous
The IAC requires teams to develop high-speed multi-agent planning algorithms to navigate autonomously around their opponents at the @IMS.

Developing algorithms which take advantage of this will allow a wider range of consumers to purchase and use driverless vehicles in their daily lives. 

#Autonomous #IAC2021 #MITDriverlessIAC2021 #MIT #SelfDrivingCars
Most deployed autonomous vehicles currently rely on proper lane segmentation and thus perform poorly when put on dirt roads or poorly marked highways.
The @MITDriverless Team believes the IAC presents a unique opportunity to develop controls and planning algorithms to exploit the unconstrained nature of the @IMS.

.@MITDriverless sees IAC as the next step for bringing the products of high speed #motorsports to the world and believes IAC will push the industry forward by influencing the design of #autonomous vehicles on public roads, making driverless vehicles more affordable and safe. https://t.co/zJNFp99gBC

account status: Today we announced Telessist, a uniquely @voyage take on remote assistance for self-driving cars! https://t.co/IOnXvHurl8
retweet status:
🦾 Introducing @voyage Telessist, combining the intelligence of a human driver with our self-driving A.I, and accelerating the delivery of fully autonomous ride-hailing services.

The robots are coming, but we humans are needed for a while longer.

https://t.co/1i8FOClOJ9

✅ Commander (our self-driving A.I.)
✅ Shield (our supercharged AEB system)
✅ Telessist
✅ FCA partnership

With this suite of self-driving technology, we are so damned close to delivering on the promise of self-driving cars.

Come and join the fun! https://t.co/dX5k77yIym

Telessist Remote Drive enables a remote operator to temporarily take over control of the vehicle and safely remote-drive it through the situation at low speed from the Telessist Pod.

Remote Drive Assist is our robust safety system that makes this incredibly safe.

3️⃣ Sometimes a situation is so complex and so wild that human control is required.

Think emergency vehicles, unpredictable crowds of pedestrians, wild-deer boxing the vehicle in, complex three-point turns, and more.

This is when Remote Drive, and Remote Drive Assist kick-in. https://t.co/PYsPch16Bg

2️⃣ When our vehicles get confused, Telessist can ask a remote operator ”what should I do here?”

The response might be simple, like "proceed at 5mph", or it might be more complex, like drawing a path through construction on a touchscreen.

This is Discrete Decision Making. https://t.co/rFKVYHRZPT

1️⃣ Monitoring provides great customer support. If a rider needs something (e.g. to re-route), they can always reach a human.

Monitoring also improves safety, asking a human to complete pre-ride checks (like verifying the perimeter of the vehicle is clear by checking cameras). https://t.co/KLFvhml1EZ

The Pod provides three key functions for our remote operators:

1️⃣ Monitoring
2️⃣ Discrete Decision Making
3️⃣ Remote Driving

🛠 All of this is made possible by the Telessist Pod–a custom-built, proprietary workstation for our remote operators. The Pod uses the same automotive-grade components as our vehicles for steering, throttle, brake, and the ECU.

For the benefits of CAVs to be realised, users must accept and trust the technology. Therefore, #FLOURISH adopted a user-focused approach to understand user needs and expectations of CAV technology, focusing on older adults and those with mobility-related conditions.
